to the editor re bush is proposing a health plan to aid the needy front page april 12 gov george w bush would grant a tax credit of 1000 to an individual to buy private health insurance but 1000 is a pitifully small fraction of the 5000 plus that an individual must pay for even basic insurance moreover by federally subsidizing private insurance companies governor bush 's plan would prolong the nightmare of health maintenance organizations which americans have increasingly deemed a failure mr bush should pretend that his proposed subsidy will do anything but throw dust in our eyes by diverting us from recognizing that national universal health care is not a privilege but a necessity like national defense james s bernstein md rockville centre ny april 12 2000

